author: Written by: Rene Brunet
title: Rene: Expect a cool, autumn feel for the remainder of the weeken
text:
NEW ORLEANS, LA (WVUE) - A cold front moved through our area late last night and brought cooler and drier air. As high pressure builds into Louisiana, skies will continue to clear through the rest of Saturday.
Tonight, lows will be on the cool side while lots of sunshine will bring us a beautiful Sunday! The coming week looks like much of the same pleasant and dry weather.
Another cold front will move through Tuesday morning simply reinforcing the pleasant weather with little chance of rain as this second front moves through.
Follow me on Twitter: @ReneBrunetFOX8
- Meteorologist Rene Brunet
